<div class="card mt-3 mb-3">
  <h4 class="card-header">Inert Atmosphere Oven PDFs</h4>
  <div class="card-header">
    <ul class="nav nav-tabs card-header-tabs"
        role="tablist">
      <%= render partial: "nav_tab",
                 locals: { id: "iao-id",
                           title: "ID Bakesheet",
                           active: true } %>
      <%= render partial: "nav_tab",
                locals: { id: "iao-bakestand",
                          title: "Bakestand Bakesheet",
                          active: false } %>
      <%= render partial: "nav_tab",
                locals: { id: "iao-final",
                          title: "Final Bakesheet",
                          active: false } %>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="tab-content">
    <div class="card-body tab-pane fade show active"
         id="iao-id"
         role="tabpanel"
         aria-labelledby="iao-id-tab">
      <%= render partial: 'sample_form',
                 locals: { action: "inert_identification_bakesheet" } %>
      <%= render partial: 'post_url',
                 locals: { url: "/inert_identification_bakesheet" } %>
      <p class="card-text">
        The <abbr title="Inert Atmosphere Oven">IAO</abbr> ID bakesheet is used
        to identify parts while they're baking (it is designed to be printed
        and displayed on the front of the oven). To generate the PDF, an object must
        be POSTed via a JSON encoded string. The container object must contain
        two properties: an integer bakestand number and an array of exactly 18
        <code>Tray</code> objects.
      </p>
      <p class="card-text">
        <em>This PDF is generated from the same exact data as the IAO bakestand
        bakesheet.</em>
      </p>
      <div class="row">
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Container",
                             code: "iao_id_object" } %>
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Tray",
                             code: "iao_tray" } %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body tab-pane fade"
         id="iao-bakestand"
         role="tabpanel"
         aria-labelledby="iao-id-tab">
      <%= render partial: 'sample_form',
                 locals: { action: "inert_bakestand_bakesheet" } %>
      <%= render partial: 'post_url',
                 locals: { url: "/inert_bakestand_bakesheet" } %>
      <p class="card-text">
        The <abbr title="Inert Atmosphere Oven">IAO</abbr> bakestand bakesheet is
        used to identify parts on a bakestand after they have been removed from the
        oven. To generate the PDF, an object must be POSTed via a JSON encoded
        string. The container object must contain two properties: an integer
        bakestand number and an array of exactly 18 <code>Tray</code> objects.
      </p>
      <p class="card-text">
        <em>This PDF is generated from the same exact data as the IAO identification
        bakesheet.</em>
      </p>
      <div class="row">
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Container",
                             code: "iao_id_object" } %>
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Tray",
                             code: "iao_tray" } %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body tab-pane fade"
         id="iao-final"
         role="tabpanel"
         aria-labelledby="iao-final-tab">
      <%= render partial: 'sample_form',
                 locals: { action: "inert_final_bakesheet" } %>
      <%= render partial: 'post_url',
                 locals: { url: "/inert_final_bakesheet" } %>
      <p class="card-text">
        The <abbr title="Inert Atmosphere Oven">IAO</abbr> final bakesheet is
        used to document the baking process and is printed and attached to
        shop orders after parts are baked. To generate the PDF, an object must
        be POSTed via a JSON encoded string. The container object must contain
        three properties: an array of exactly 18 <code>Tray</code> objects, a
        <code>Timestamps</code> object, and an array of <code>Status
        Reading</code> objects.
      </p>
      <div class="row">
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Container",
                             code: "iao_final_object" } %>
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Tray",
                             code: "iao_tray" } %>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Timestamps",
                             code: "iao_timestamps" } %>
        <%= render partial: 'object_card',
                   locals: { heading: "Status Reading",
                             code: "iao_status_reading" } %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>